CAPE TOWN - There's been another robbery on a Golden Arrow bus. Two robbers posing as passengers boarded a bus in Khayelitsha on Wednesday morning. They then held up commuters, making off with money, cellphones and other items. "They then jumped out of the bus and fled the scene on foot. The docket will be transferred to Gugulethu West police for further investigation as the incident occurred in their jurisdiction," said the police's Frederick van Wyk. Over the past several years, bus robberies have been increasing in the city. Download the Eyewitness News app to your iOS  or Android  device.